<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36">^</a></b> <a href="#CITEREFLehmann1998">Lehmann 1998</a>, p.&#160;75. The dating of Sangam literature and the identification of its language with Old Tamil have recently been questioned by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Herman_Tieken&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Herman Tieken (page does not exist)">Herman Tieken</a> who argues that the works are better understood as 9th century <a href="/w/index.php?title=Pandyan_dynasty&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Pandyan dynasty (page does not exist)">Pāṇṭiyan dynasty</a> compositions, deliberately written in an archaising style to make them seem older than they were (<a href="#CITEREFTieken2001">Tieken 2001</a>). Tieken's dating has, however, been criticised by reviewers of his work. See e.g. <a href="#CITEREFHart2004">Hart 2004</a>, <a href="#CITEREFFerro-Luzzi2001">Ferro-Luzzi 2001</a>, <a href="#CITEREFMonius2002">Monius 2002</a> and <a href="#CITEREFWilden2003">Wilden 2003</a></li>
